cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SI 

This paper is about formal verification and differential privacy, which are both topics in computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses probability measures and composition theorems, which are related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of liftings and quantification over sets of samples suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) or data science (cs.DS) perspective. Finally, the paper proposes a new construction for approximate lifting, which could be considered a contribution to the field of statistical inference (cs.SI).
